From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Skip RTS registration at Stage0 for cross-version bootstrap

When using GHC 9.6.7 to bootstrap GHC 9.2.8 on Windows, Stage0 utilities
link against bootstrap libraries (base-4.18.x) which expect bootstrap's
RTS symbols (stg_ap_0_fast, newCAF, stg_gc_unpt_r1, etc.).

The previous patch attempted to copy bootstrap's RTS to Stage0, but the
function continued after the copy and called copyConf for RTS again.
This broke package registration because:

1. copyConf unregisters packages by NAME (not version)
2. RTS at Stage0 should use bootstrap's RTS from global DB, not local copy
3. The case statement matched RTS as isBoot (RTS not in stagePackages Stage0)

This patch:
- Adds skipRtsAtStage0 guard to prevent RTS from going through copyConf
- Adds skipRtsAtStage0 guard to prevent RTS from going through buildConf
- Copies bootstrap's RTS .conf file (with --expand-pkgroot) for dependencies
- Uses 'ghc-pkg update' to register the copied .conf in Stage0 package DB

This allows Stage0 utilities to link against bootstrap's RTS library while
maintaining .conf file presence for dependency resolution.

--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs	2025-12-20 20:55:14.162546140 -0600
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs	2025-12-20 20:55:58.186434476 -0600
@@ -15,6 +15,7 @@
 import Settings
 import Target
 import Utilities
+import Data.Maybe (catMaybes)

 import Hadrian.Haskell.Cabal.Type
 import qualified Text.Parsec      as Parsec
@@ -43,16 +44,7 @@
